<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" dir="ltr">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Store - DuoHacker</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="mainTitle">
      <div class="title">
        Store
        <!--<span class="titleLinks">Navigation</span>-->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="itemlist">
      <% products.forEach(function(item){ %>
      <div class="storeitem" onclick="buy(<%= item.id %>);">
        <img src="images/<%= item.image %>"/><br>
        <div class="productBorder"></div>
        <b class="productName"><%= item.name %></b><br>
        <p class="productPrice"><%= item.price/100 %>â‚¬</p>
      </div>
      <% }) %>
    </div>
    <div class="info">
      <div class="infoBorder"></div>
      <h2>Informations</h2><br>
      <p>DuoHacker is a tool to get unlimited XP on Duolingo. Access to DuoHacker requires a key, which you a able to buy in the store. There are diffrent keys with diffrent possibilities and limits, but before actually buying a key you get the chance to try out DuoHacker by requesting a <b>trial key</b>, which is totally free, but with a limit of <%= products[0].limit %> XP per day and validity of 24 hours, which will start counting right after receiving the key. The <b>Common Key</b> has a limit of <%= products[1].limit %> XP per day and like the other paid keys won't expire. The <b>Special Key</b> has a limit of <%= products[2].limit %> XP per day and the <b>Admin Key</b> <%= products[3].limit %> XP per day, what is more than you would ever need.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info">
      <div class="infoBorder"></div>
      <h2>Contact</h2><br>
      <p>Feel free to contact me on my <a href="https://discord.gg/DXAwvrW">Discord</a>, I will try to give you help as soon as possible.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="footer">
      &copy;Lolo 2019
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
<script type="text/javascript">

  function buy(id){

    const form = document.createElement('form');
    form.method = "post";
    form.action = "./info";

    const hiddenField = document.createElement('input');
    hiddenField.type = 'hidden';
    hiddenField.name = "id";
    hiddenField.value = id;

    form.appendChild(hiddenField);

    document.body.appendChild(form);
    form.submit();
  }

</script>
